description:
&lt;p&gt;To support the work of the Population Health Team hosted by Morecambe Bay CCG we wish to recruit administration support for 22.5 hours per week on a fixed term contract/secondment basis until the end of March 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the work of the Population Health Team and Bay Health and Care Partners we are seeking to recruit administration support to help meet increasing demands on the team. For the right candidate this is an opportunity to work within a dynamic team with a passion for reducing inequalities in health through effective partnership working and working differently with our communities. It is challenging times and we are looking for candidates who can work as part of a wider team and bring energy and focus at this important time for Population Health, the NHS and they communities we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work will involve providing administration support at key meetings across Morecambe Bay which will enable insight into the partnership working across the Bay around Population Health. The successful candidate with have good communication skills as regular liaison with a range of organisations across Morecambe Bay will be a key part of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role presents an opportunity for the right candidate to get a deeper insight into Population Health and Population Health Management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAnji StokesJob titlePopulation Health ManagerEmail addressanji.stokes1@morecambebayccg.nhs.ukTelephone number07495629175&lt;/p&gt;
